Communicate with Professor or stakeholder Often
Plan the next step before the group separates.
Make sure everyone has something to do while the group is apart.
Have a singular vision for the team.
Have team building early and regularly.
Define Process model early.
Exploration projects should be throw away projects.
First write down your vision or dream for the final outcome as group.
Don't force any team member into one role. In contrast, roles should shift. Let everyone have the opportunity to have an experience in a different role.



